üöÄ Getting Started

1. Install Dependencies

npm install


2. Configure Environment

Open the .env file.

Update the DATABASE_URL with your real database credentials.

{{#if (eq databaseType "mysql")}}
Example for MySQL:
DATABASE_URL="mysql://root:password@localhost:3306/mydb"
{{/if}}
{{#if (eq databaseType "postgresql")}}
Example for PostgreSQL:
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/mydb?schema=public"
{{/if}}
{{#if (eq databaseType "mongodb")}}
Example for MongoDB:
DATABASE_URL="mongodb+srv://user:password@cluster.mongodb.net/mydb"
{{/if}}

3. Sync Database

Push the schema to your database to create the tables.

npx prisma db push


4. Start the Server

npm run dev


The server will start at http://localhost:3000.

